The paper discusses the use of Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) for irregular data domains modeled using a graph. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories related to machine learning and computer vision. 

cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely category as the paper proposes new architectures for CNNs using multiple-input multiple-output (MIMO) graph filters, which is a machine learning technique. 

cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is also likely as the paper deals with signals whose support can be modeled using a graph. 

cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is another possible category as CNNs are widely used in computer vision tasks, and the paper discusses their application to irregular data domains. 

cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also possible as the paper deals with neural networks and proposes new architectures for CNNs. 

cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with machine learning techniques and their application to irregular data domains.
